What an honor to be able to use Artistic Activism to make a difference 🙏🏾. Thank you #UrbanProWeekly for highlighting @chimerathefilm on the front cover. 

Please support if you can or share to help us bring awareness to all of the missing BIPOC women, that aren’t being looked for. 🙏🏾 (link in bio) 

Thank you again @tqthewriter.81 for selecting me to bring your vision to life 🙏🏾.

I finally saw my first Broadway play! It was phenomenal! There’s nothing like live theatre. So, I punched imposter syndrome in the face, and will also manifest that in addition to television and film, I will eventually be in a Broadway play (posting this so I can use it as a throwback when my manifestation becomes reality). It always seemed so unattainable to me, but my new outlook is to “Shoot for the moon. Because even if you miss, you are bound to land among the stars.”

If you’ve been following me for a while, then you know Theatre is my foundation. I was in my first production at the Cleveland Playhouse Theatre at 11 years old and it’s on that stage that solidified my career goals. I still get that overwhelmingly good feeling in my gut when acting today, but nothing compares to the audience’s live reaction in theatre. There’s no stopping for a cut, you have to really KNOW your lines and everyones, to improv on the spot if necessary. The energy is just incomparable… Stay tuned 🎭🎬

I’m absolutely blessed and grateful for every character that I’m able to portray, but when the opportunity is given to evoke change through artistry, it’s a reminder from God as to why I do what I do. As an Actress, my goal is to convey truthful human behavior in fictitious situations, and the the portrayal of Loren in @chimerathefilm was beyond that, it was spiritual. 

This was also my first role Directed, Produced, and Written by an African American Woman, @tqthewriter.81. Women represent less than 22% of Directors and 33% of film Writers in Hollywood. Let’s eliminate gender bias in this industry, so more women and girls can see themselves accurately reflected 🙏🏾❤️.

I got in! I’m going to Yale! 

Yes, theee Ivy League! 😱😭

I got accepted into Yale’s Summer Session Conservatory for Actors! 

A huge thanks to the industry professionals I’ve worked with, who wrote incredible recommendation letters on my behalf 🥹😭🙏🏾💙.

Recently I’ve been reading biographies and studying award winning Actors & Actresses. I noticed one common denominator, an Ivy League education from Yale, or they attended Juilliard. Although I can’t rewind the hands of time, I wanted an undergraduate education majoring in Theater/Drama, instead of the MBA in Marketing I eventually obtained, I can still further my education (you are never “too old” to learn). I spent years mastering the field of Marketing, while squeezing in acting classes around my day jobs.

I’m ridding my survival plan B (Marketing) and going full force back to plan A (Acting). I don’t want to be just “good”, I want to become the best I can in the field of acting. 

Although I won’t be there for fours years, I’m staying on campus for a month at Yale for the acting intensive! The same grounds of which alumni such as Angela Bassett, Meryl Streep, Sanaa Lathan, Lupita Nyong’o, and more, graduated from. 

I truly feel like a kid going to their first day of school! Counting down the months! I can’t wait to  see how far this additional training takes me 🙏🏾❤️. 

I’ll be vlogging this Summer about my journey! 
#Staytuned 🎬🙏🏾❤️

PS: In this industry, many have said no, there is so much rejection, but one of the top acting schools in this country said…YES. Thank you God 🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾. Keep dreaming y’all, and pivot if anyone or anything gets in your way! But never, NEVER give up!

2.5 months ago I started boxing, preparing to get in better shape for a role, after being inspired when I watched #Creed3… Well the writers are striking (rightfully so), and the industry is at a standstill-meaning union work has stopped (including booked work 🥹)… but, definitely practicing “staying ready so I don’t have to get ready” in my downtime. If you start something new today, can you imagine the progress you’ll make 3 months from now, 3 years from now!?

“Even the greatest was once a beginner.
Don’t be afraid to take that first step.
- #MuhammadAli 🥊

Don’t be discouraged, learn a new skill, take some new classes. It will surely pay off 🙏🏾❤️.
Out of the office 🏝️
Hanging upside down in the air in the jungle + jumping into cenotes (after being terrified but having a group of strangers cheer you on) + swimming in natural fresh water pools = living 🌊
Sometimes God puts a hold on your blessings because of who you are connected to… When you connect with the right people, your life drastically changes. I am a witness! 🙏🏾🙌🏾🥹😭

I’m vlogging “My Summer at Yale” on my new YouTube channel 💜. Subscribe to follow my journey as I elevate my acting career at Yale University! So grateful to God for 2nd chances 🙏🏾 and the people He strategically placed in my life who truly believe in me and helped make this happen (Yale ain’t cheap yall 🫠🥹)! 

For years, I regretted not pursuing my Bachelor’s and Master’s in Theatre like most of the greats you see on Broadway, in TV and film, and settling for my plan B- an MBA in Marketing… now I get a redo 😭🙏🏾🙌🏾. 

It’s never too late and you are never too old- Dreams don’t have expiration dates!

Now please subscribe, so I can get this YouTube 💰😘.

I’m forever grateful to @tqthewriter.81 for selecting me to portray “Loren”. 

“I created this film to honor the women who have suffered from media apathy; those missing and murdered women of color and trans women who didn't get the attention that they needed. Countless names will go unknown, unspoken, and only remembered by their loved ones. This film is for them and for the women fortunate enough to be alive to tell their stories. Our voices must be heard.”

~ @tqthewriter.81

I’m absolutely blessed and grateful for every character that I’m able to portray, but when the opportunity is given to invoke change through artistry, it’s a reminder from God as to why I do what I do. And that’s a wrap on 5 intensive weeks at one of the top acting programs in the world! 

Not only am I better actor, I am a better human. Thank you tremendously to all of the Professors, the TA’s, all of the Conservatory Actors, and @yalesummersession. It was such a blessing to be able to dedicate approximately 840 hours to becoming a better Actress and being able to truly be myself, surrounded by other artists. I am forever changed.

I will truly miss you all! 🥹😭

*I tried to tag everyone, but I could only tag 20 🥹*

Another blessed year of life, grateful is an understatement 🙏🏾🎂❤️.

I first heard about #Juilliard in 2001, from the film “Save the Last Dance”. I didn’t even think about attempting to apply when I was graduating because I didn’t feel qualified.- I hadn’t danced since I was three, I never took vocal classes at that time, and had only been in school plays and performed in one at the Cleveland Playhouse Theatre. 

I thank God for second chances. I’m grateful I got the opportunity to audition for Juilliard’s extension program for actors and got in! 🙏🏾💙

Staying sharp during this strike and always will be a forever student of the craft💪🏾 🎭

What an honor it is to portray “Ruth Younger” in Cincinnati Black Theatre Company’s upcoming production of “A Raisin in the Sun” October 26th-29th at the Artsville Theatre in #Cincinnati!🙌🏾🙏🏾🎭

I was enamored when I first witnessed Ruby Dee, a phenomenal actress who paved the way for so many African American entertainers (she was also from #Cleveland by the way, and a member of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc. 😉🔺), as "Ruth Younger". She originated the role in both the stage and film versions of “A Raisin in the Sun”.

There is nothing like the instant gratification of performing in front of a live audience. I am so excited and grateful for the opportunity to get get back on stage and have a creative outlet amidst this #SAGAFTRA strike (live theatre performances are permitted). 

If you are in the #Cincinnati area, come check us out 🙏🏾. 

Ticket details coming soon!
AIR B&D Dropping on @tubi VERY soon 🎥🔥

#Cincinnati Black #Theatre presents “A Raisin in the Sun” October 26th-29th at #Artsville. Swipe for more information and tickets 🙏🏾❤️. 

#rehearsalbts #bts #blacktheatre #araisininthesun #cincinnatitheatre #cincinnatiactors

Although this #SAGAFTRAstrike is necessary, it’s been difficult as a creative. Not to mention projects you’ve booked, that you can’t promote (work begets work 😩). Jobs you’ve prayed for and worked so hard for, end or are canceled because of the lengthy duration of the strike. This is an industry of pivoting though and I’m blessed to be able to still have a creative outlet in theatre. I hadn’t been in a play since 2019, upon which the tour stopped due to Covid…. Whew, this acting journey has been a tumultuous one, especially the past 4 years for us all. Stay strong fellow Actors 🎭💪🏾🙏🏾❤️. 

It’s such an honor to portray “Ruth Younger” in Cincinnati Black Theatre Company’s production of “A Raisin in the Sun”. Come check us out October 26th-29th at Artsville in #Cincinnati Ohio.

Thank you to everyone who has supported, watched, shared, texted, called, dm-ed, etc. about Air B&D on @tubi and making it #1 in multiple categories this week! 

Keep in mind, we shot this indie film in 5 DAYS! That’s a great feat, especially for Actors (when you have maybe at most a chance for 2 takes per scene/ but mostly 1). 

For a larger budget/ studio film, on average it can take about 146 days in pre-production, 106 days to shoot, and 301 days in post-production or longer.

So a huge congratulations to all of the cast and crew of @hwicfilmworks’ #AirBnD! We made it look easy, but it’s not 😅💕🙌🏾.

Loving all the feedback and love for Air B&D, wish I could like and share all the posts and comments! 💕💕💕

#Repost from @yalesummersession 

“Last summer, actress and producer Brittany Mayti was a student in the Yale Summer Conservatory for Actors. Listen to her tell her story about this five-week experience!

The Yale Summer Conservatory for Actors is an intensive introduction to the basic techniques of acting. Based on the principles of Stanislavski, this program at Yale focuses on building a foundation that is applicable to all further study in theater, allowing students to discover new skills, a deeper understanding of craft, and a more liberated sense of permission and play. Under the guidance of theater professionals who work regularly in regional and New York theaters, as well as in film and television, these students work in small groups and get individual attention in order to grow, both as performers, and as people.

#yale #yalecollege #yaleuniversity #ivyleague #yalesummersession #yss #yssyoucan”

2023 has truly been blessing after blessing for my acting career, praise God! From starring in @hwicfilmworks Air B&D, the release of the film “Locked In” and being mentioned in the New York Times, to filming my first Christmas movie (coming soon to @betplus), the private screening of @tqthewriter.81’s short film Loren’s Chimera, modeling in regional print campaigns (coming soon), booking some amazing projects (and them being cancelled due to the strike 🥹😭, but thank God nonetheless), being accepted and attending Yale University’s Summer Conservatory for Actors, getting back into Theatre since 2019 and portraying “Ruth Younger” in one of my favorite plays “A Raisin in the Sun”, being nominated and winning @ohio_entertainment_awards 2023 best Actress award, being accepted and attending Juilliard’s extension program this semester, and being nominated by @thecoriluvshow’s audience pick as one of top 12 actresses of 2023! This year was truly an example of “faith without works is dead”. I say this all not to brag, but hopefully be a testimony to someone who has a dream, because I worked extremely hard this year and prayed my butt off! One of my friends calls me the pivoting Queen and I receive that because I refuse to do the same thing over and over again and expect different results. 2024, I’m ready for you 🙌🏾🙏🏾! 

PS: go to @thecoriluvshow’s website and vote this week 🙏🏾❤️
